
Benchmark 1 – Cloud-Based Damage Classification System
Development of a cloud-hosted AI model (AWS or equivalent) capable of:
Identifying shoe type and brand (where the dataset allows)
Classifying material type
Detecting and categorizing damage (oxidation, scuffs, separation, paint wear)
Performance Requirements:
≥95% classification consistency
Deviation limited to ±1 classification band
Repeatability across 100 identical scans
Inference time configurable between 1–4 seconds

Benchmark 2 – Cloud-Based Repair Recommendation Engine
Development of a cloud-based system capable of:
Generating recommended repair actions
Producing structured service outputs
Providing cost estimation logic integration
Performance Requirements:
≥95% output consistency across repeated scans
Structured output format compatible with Company workflow systems

Benchmark 3 – Enclosure & Scan Consistency Integration
Integration of AI system into Company-designated scan enclosure, ensuring:
Stable camera input processing
Consistent lighting normalization
Repeatable scan conditions
Functional demonstration must show:
Consistent outputs across controlled test scans
Error deviation ≤5% across identical scan trials

Benchmark 4 – Local Deployment & Training System
Deployment of a locally executable AI model capable of:
Running without continuous cloud dependency
Being retrained using Company-provided datasets
Maintaining ≥95% classification consistency after local deployment
